00:05:01.160 --> 00:05:01.660
Correct.

00:05:01.660 --> 00:05:03.540
It's called the optical power.

00:05:03.540 --> 00:05:06.570
And it is actually
the first instance

00:05:06.570 --> 00:05:08.970
that we saw this quantity.

00:05:08.970 --> 00:05:12.620
It is the inverse
distance units.

00:05:12.620 --> 00:05:14.760
But we don't call
it inverse meters.

00:05:14.760 --> 00:05:18.450
We call it-- how do we call
the unit of this quantity?

00:05:18.450 --> 00:05:20.835
Diopters, right?

