by the distance
times the tangent

00:14:01.270 --> 00:14:04.030
of the angle of propagation.

00:14:04.030 --> 00:14:06.450
But of course, with the
paraxial approximations,

00:14:06.450 --> 00:14:09.533
instead of the tangent
we put the angle itself.

00:14:09.533 --> 00:14:11.200
So this is what this
equation says here.

00:14:11.200 --> 00:14:15.280
If you multiply this by this,
the indices of refraction

00:14:15.280 --> 00:14:16.430
will drop out.

00:14:16.430 --> 00:14:20.680
And you're left with d,
the distance times alpha.

00:14:20.680 --> 00:14:24.880
So it is really the tangent.

00:14:24.880 --> 00:14:25.750
So this seems silly.

00:14:25.750 --> 00:14:28.030
But the reason we did
it is so that when

00:14:28.030 --> 00:14:32.650
we have optical systems with
a cascade of uniform space

00:14:32.650 --> 00:14:36.010
then add the refractive
interface and then more uniform

00:14:36.010 --> 00:14:38.620
space and so on, then
you can basically

00:14:38.620 --> 00:14:42.260
ray trace those systems simply
by cascading these matrices.

00:14:42.260 --> 00:14:44.950
So this is why we did
this particular pattern.

00:14:44.950 --> 00:14:46.990
But this really doesn't
say anything other

00:14:46.990 --> 00:14:50.560
than rays must propagate
in a straight line

00:14:50.560 --> 00:14:54.100
in uniform refractive index
because that is the shortest

00:14:54.100 --> 00:14:58.200
path for them to follow.

00:14:58.200 --> 00:15:01.740
And then what we did, after
we developed this formulation,

00:15:01.740 --> 00:15:05.670
is we actually put into practice
in the special case of two

00:15:05.670 --> 00:15:10.650
adjacent spherical surfaces.

00:15:10.650 --> 00:15:14.970
So typically, you
have air outside.

00:15:14.970 --> 00:15:17.400
And between the two
surfaces, you have glass.

00:15:17.400 --> 00:15:19.170
And this kind of
element is what we call

00:15:19.170 --> 00:15:21.060
in everyday language a lens.

00:15:21.060 --> 00:15:22.290
It does not have to be glass.

00:15:22.290 --> 00:15:24.630
For example, in the case of
our eyes, it's not glass.

00:15:24.630 --> 00:15:30.210
It is actually tissue,
mostly water in fact.

00:15:30.210 --> 00:15:33.070
But anyway, it is higher
index of refraction

00:15:33.070 --> 00:15:34.500
than the surrounding air.

00:15:34.500 --> 00:15:35.785
So it is acting--

00:15:35.785 --> 00:15:39.650
it is doing the
same job as a lens.

00:15:39.650 --> 00:15:42.290
And what we did then, if you
recall, I will not do all of it

00:15:42.290 --> 00:15:45.860
again is but what we did is we
did a cascade of the matrices

00:15:45.860 --> 00:15:47.510
for the two interfaces.

00:15:47.510 --> 00:15:51.170
And based on this, we derived
the properties of this element.

00:15:51.170 --> 00:15:53.450
And what we discovered
is the basic properties

00:15:53.450 --> 00:15:56.450
that if you have had a ray
bundle that is arriving

00:15:56.450 --> 00:15:59.630
from infinity, therefore
it is razor parallel,

00:15:59.630 --> 00:16:01.670
this type of optical
element will actually

00:16:01.670 --> 00:16:03.050
bring them to a focus.

00:16:03.050 --> 00:16:06.710
So the rays after, they will
propagate a certain distance

00:16:06.710 --> 00:16:08.160
after the element.

00:16:08.160 --> 00:16:10.350
And then they will
focus to a point.

00:16:10.350 --> 00:16:12.440
And we also derive the
other useful quantities,

00:16:12.440 --> 00:16:14.970
we derive the elevation
of this point.

00:16:14.970 --> 00:16:16.910
We discover that
it is proportional

00:16:16.910 --> 00:16:21.110
to this focal distance times
the annual propagation.

00:16:21.110 --> 00:16:23.210
And then we saw that
there's different cases

00:16:23.210 --> 00:16:26.480
of focusing depending on
the nature of the lens.

00:16:26.480 --> 00:16:30.330
Namely its optical power.

00:16:30.330 --> 00:16:34.610
So positive lens will focus
the rays at a finite distance.

00:16:34.610 --> 00:16:37.410
A negative lens will actually
cause the rays to diverge.

00:16:37.410 --> 00:16:40.170
So they, strictly
speaking, do not focus.

00:16:40.170 --> 00:16:42.140
But if you extend
them backwards,

00:16:42.140 --> 00:16:44.690
then that create what is
called a virtual image.

00:16:44.690 --> 00:16:48.830
And we will see later today
what exactly this virtual image

00:16:48.830 --> 00:16:52.190
means and why it is an
extremely useful concept

00:16:52.190 --> 00:16:53.600
in optical design.

00:16:53.600 --> 00:16:55.220
For now, it appears
as an oddity.

00:16:55.220 --> 00:16:56.210
What exactly is that?

00:16:56.210 --> 00:16:59.560
Why did it move-- why did
it trace the rays backwards.

00:16:59.560 --> 00:17:04.963
But today, actually, you
will see why this is useful.

00:17:04.963 --> 00:17:06.380
The main point to
take out of here

00:17:06.380 --> 00:17:09.619
is that the lens is acting
kind of like a lever.

00:17:09.619 --> 00:17:11.906
So if you have--

00:17:11.906 --> 00:17:16.910
if you imagine that you
are rotating the angle

00:17:16.910 --> 00:17:19.910
that the rays are arriving
to the left of the lens,

00:17:19.910 --> 00:17:23.480
then this point is
moving linearly.

00:17:23.480 --> 00:17:26.150
It is staying on this
plane, ideally at least,

00:17:26.150 --> 00:17:27.920
within the paraxial
approximation.

00:17:27.920 --> 00:17:31.880
It is staying on this
plane but it is moving.

00:17:31.880 --> 00:17:36.970
So as you rotate the angle,
the elevation changes.

00:17:36.970 --> 00:17:39.760
And the constant of
proportionality in this change

00:17:39.760 --> 00:17:41.570
is the focal length of the lens.

00:17:41.570 --> 00:17:45.190
This is a very key point
to remember about lenses

00:17:45.190 --> 00:17:48.160
and how they function.

00:17:48.160 --> 00:17:51.400
And the other thing that
we said is that it can also

00:17:51.400 --> 00:17:53.140
work the other way around.

00:17:53.140 --> 00:17:57.000
If you take this
picture, the rule

00:17:57.000 --> 00:18:00.720
is that the rays always go
from the left to the right.

00:18:00.720 --> 00:18:02.285
It's not a rule,
it is a convention.

00:18:02.285 --> 00:18:04.410
There's no physical law,
obviously, that says that.

00:18:04.410 --> 00:18:06.720
But it's a convention.

00:18:06.720 --> 00:18:08.580
But nevertheless,
there is a physical law

00:18:08.580 --> 00:18:15.030
that says that if a light
propagates in one direction

00:18:15.030 --> 00:18:17.410
and then you flip
the time backwards,

00:18:17.410 --> 00:18:20.130
that is you reverse the
propagation of the light,

00:18:20.130 --> 00:18:23.060
then the physical law actually
says that the propagation

00:18:23.060 --> 00:18:24.570
should remain invariant.

00:18:24.570 --> 00:18:28.930
That is if I knew that the light
propagated this way focuses,

00:18:28.930 --> 00:18:31.800
if I turn time backwards
like these old movies

00:18:31.800 --> 00:18:34.020
that you see where they
play the movie backwards

00:18:34.020 --> 00:18:37.110
and you see it pass, you
know, moving towards the back.

00:18:37.110 --> 00:18:40.710
If I did that, I would have
the rays going like this.

00:18:40.710 --> 00:18:42.240
So this against our convention.

00:18:42.240 --> 00:18:44.560
So that's why I flipped it here.

00:18:44.560 --> 00:18:47.100
Now again, the rays are
going from left to right

00:18:47.100 --> 00:18:49.950
but in this case they're
going through the focus.

00:18:49.950 --> 00:18:54.360
What this picture is telling us
is that if you have rays that

00:18:54.360 --> 00:18:58.980
originate at the point one
focal distance behind the lens,

00:18:58.980 --> 00:19:01.510
then this will form
an image at infinity.

00:19:01.510 --> 00:19:04.500
That is, the lens will
collimate this ray bundle.

00:19:04.500 --> 00:19:07.405
And it will send the
rays out parallel at a 90

00:19:07.405 --> 00:19:09.030
that obeys, actually
if you look at it,

00:19:09.030 --> 00:19:12.240
is the same relationship
that was obeyed before.

00:19:12.240 --> 00:19:14.230
With the next reminder sign.

00:19:14.230 --> 00:19:15.930
And why did the minus
sign come about?

00:19:25.573 --> 00:19:27.740
Everything's symmetric here
except for this annoying

00:19:27.740 --> 00:19:28.560
minus sign.

00:19:28.560 --> 00:19:29.600
Why has this come about?

00:19:45.344 --> 00:19:47.840
Button.

