00:24:00.950 --> 00:24:04.040
So this was true for what
we call the thin lens, where

00:24:04.040 --> 00:24:08.330
it is thin because we
assume that the distance

00:24:08.330 --> 00:24:12.500
between the surfaces within
the paraxial approximation

00:24:12.500 --> 00:24:14.970
can be neglected.

00:24:14.970 --> 00:24:20.070
If we cannot do that, if we
cannot neglect the distance

00:24:20.070 --> 00:24:24.990
between the two surfaces, our
formulation does not abandon

00:24:24.990 --> 00:24:28.050
us, we just get a more
complicated formula.

00:24:28.050 --> 00:24:32.610
And the reason the formula
becomes more complicated

00:24:32.610 --> 00:24:37.410
is because if we drop
the approximation

00:24:37.410 --> 00:24:40.740
of negligible
spacing then the ray

00:24:40.740 --> 00:24:43.480
refracts twice before exiting.

00:24:43.480 --> 00:24:45.620
It will diffract at
the first interface

00:24:45.620 --> 00:24:48.480
and the second interface.

00:24:48.480 --> 00:24:49.800
We'll get the formula for this.

00:24:49.800 --> 00:24:52.950
The thick lens, I don't want
to go back into the formula.

00:24:52.950 --> 00:24:54.900
It just comes out
of the algebra.

00:24:54.900 --> 00:24:56.970
What I really want to
emphasize in this case

00:24:56.970 --> 00:25:01.020
is that even though
the refracts doubly,

00:25:01.020 --> 00:25:04.740
we can pretend that it
only refracted once.

00:25:04.740 --> 00:25:09.240
And we can do that by
extending the incoming ray,

00:25:09.240 --> 00:25:11.460
extending the outgoing ray.

00:25:11.460 --> 00:25:15.780
And then what the plane,
where they intersect,

00:25:15.780 --> 00:25:18.210
that is called the
principal plane.

00:25:18.210 --> 00:25:21.460
Actually that is called
the second principal plane.

00:25:21.460 --> 00:25:25.100
If I do it for an
incoming ray bundle that

00:25:25.100 --> 00:25:28.360
is imaged at infinity then
it is the other way around.

00:25:28.360 --> 00:25:32.110
Again, it can extend the
incoming ray, the outgoing ray,

00:25:32.110 --> 00:25:34.930
and again get the
first principal plane.

00:25:34.930 --> 00:25:37.270
And the reason we did
all this exercise were

00:25:37.270 --> 00:25:40.480
to discover principal
planes and so on

00:25:40.480 --> 00:25:42.740
is because this
allows us to do ray

00:25:42.740 --> 00:25:44.350
tracing as shown over there.

