01:05:21.010 --> 01:05:22.010
PROFESSOR: That's right.

01:05:22.010 --> 01:05:22.850
That's one way.

01:05:22.850 --> 01:05:25.640
If you make the
mirror like this,

01:05:25.640 --> 01:05:28.490
now the mirror has a
positive R therefore

01:05:28.490 --> 01:05:31.430
it has a negative
F. Now this mirror

01:05:31.430 --> 01:05:33.980
has become the equivalent
of a negative lens.

01:05:33.980 --> 01:05:36.470
Therefore it will
form a virtual image.

01:05:36.470 --> 01:05:39.420
What's another possibility
for forming a virtual image

01:05:39.420 --> 01:05:40.170
with a mirror?

01:05:44.710 --> 01:05:46.150
What about a positive lens?

01:05:46.150 --> 01:05:49.546
Could a positive lens
